{"title": "Sikh Religion: Its Gurus, Sacred Writings and Authors, Volume 1", "description": "Michael MacAuliffe (also known as Max Arthur Macauliffe) was a senior British administrator, prolific scholar and author. Macauliffe is renowned for his translation of Sikh scripture and history into English.<br /><br />This is one of the first (and still one of the few) comprehensive books about the Sikh religion in the English language. MacAuliffe had extensive access to manuscripts of the Sikh sacred writings (the Granth), as well as support from Sikh scholars and leaders of the time. This volume, volume one of six, covers Guru Nanak, the founder of Sikhism.<br /><br />Coordinated by JoeD & Sachin.", "duration": 51119, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "5907", "name": " Max Arthur Macauliffe"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/sikhreligion_1504_librivox/sikh_religion1_1504.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Other religions"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "JoeD"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Rapunzelina"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Preface part a", "readers": [4034], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/sikhreligion_1504_librivox/sikhreligion1_01_macauliffe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1210}, {"section": 2, "title": "Preface part b", "readers": [7104], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/sikhreligion_1504_librivox/sikhreligion1_02_macauliffe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1556}, {"section": 3, "title": "Preface part c", "readers": [7104], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/sikhreligion_1504_librivox/sikhreligion1_03_macauliffe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1381}, {"section": 4, "title": "Introduction Chapter 1", "readers": [4034], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/sikhreligion_1504_librivox/sikhreligion1_04_macauliffe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1627}, {"section": 5, "title": "Introduction Chapter 2", "r